- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely category as the paper discusses decision-theoretic planning techniques, which are a core topic in AI. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the DRIPS planning system, which involves programming language concepts such as abstraction. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper discusses generating search control information, which can be seen as a machine learning task. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as decision-theoretic planning is a key component of robotics. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses evaluating the efficiency of the DRIPS system, which is a software engineering concern.
